{{Lunisolar November}} '''November 19''' is the 19th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Shōkyō|ja|正恭|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year / {{ill|Kenmu|ja|建武|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1336]] [[January 2]]) – {{ill|Nitta Yoshisada|ja|新田義貞|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and his forces departed Kyoto to pursue {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|足利尊氏|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 9th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1566]] [[December 30]]) – {{ill|Mōri Motonari|ja|毛利元就|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} defeated {{ill|Amako Yoshiaki|ja|尼子義久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} at Tomida Tsukiyama Castle, leading to the extinction of the Amako clan. * {{ill|Kansei|ja|寛政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1790]] [[January 4]]) – {{ill|Tanikaze Kajinosuke (2nd)|ja|谷風梶之助|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} received permission for the first yokozuna ring-entering ceremony.
== Births == * {{ill|Genna|ja|元和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1624]] [[January 9]]) – {{ill|Meisei Tennō|ja|明正天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 109th Emperor of Japan (died [[1696]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1828]] [[January 5]]) – {{ill|Kobayashi Issa|ja|小林一茶|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a haiku poet (born [[1763]]).
